{
  "name": "Email → Leads (lead-intake)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Email → Leads\n1. Open the **Email Trigger** node → add your **IMAP** credentials (Gmail/Outlook/any provider). For Gmail use an App Password.\n2. Open the **POST to lead-intake** node → in the URL, replace **YOUR_TOKEN** with the token from the console (Settings → Lead capture).\n3. **Activate** the workflow (top-right toggle).\n\nEvery new inquiry email is sent to your lead-intake function, which parses it and creates a lead in the CRM.",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 360
      },
      "id": "note1",
      "name": "How to set up",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [200, 120]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "format": "simple",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "imap1",
      "name": "Email Trigger (IMAP)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.emailReadImap",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [620, 320]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://tbxzxfjumlnciczizols.supabase.co/functions/v1/lead-intake?channel=email&t=YOUR_TOKEN",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ { \"from\": ($json.from || \"\"), \"subject\": ($json.subject || \"\"), \"body\": ($json.text || $json.textHtml || \"\"), \"ext_id\": ($json.messageId || \"\") } }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "http1",
      "name": "POST to lead-intake",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [900, 320]
    }
